    "sections": [
        {
            "name": "Description",
            "type": "section",
            "html": "Young walruses start out with gray hides, but their flesh becomes almost pinkish when they reach old age (20\u201330 years for most walruses). Their hide is up to 4 inches thick, with another 6 inches of blubber hidden underneath that, accounting for their incredible toughness\u2014and for their usefulness to arctic cultures as a source of meat and fuel."
        }
    ],
